http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Free-liver-check-up-camp/article14013856.ece

The NIMS Institute of Liver Studies and Research and The Hindu are jointly organising a free liver check-up and awareness camp as a part of a Comprehensive Liver and Digestive Healthcare initiative on January 31 at Sri Moolam Club, Vazhuthacaud.The most common cause of fatty liver is alcoholism and heavy drinking (alcoholic fatty liver disease). But in the past 30 years, non-alcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD), a condition caused by the build-up of fat in the liver because of obesity and sedentary lifestyle, has been on the rise.The camp will provide blood tests, liver scan (fibro scan) and ultrasound scan for free for the detection of fatty liver disease, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, cirrhosis, gall stones, liver cancer and gastro-intestinal cancer.Hepatology, gastroenterology and surgical gastroenterology consultations will also be provided for free.The medical camp will start at 8 a.m. on January 31 and will be led by a team of expert doctors and surgeons.PackagesSpecial packages are also on offer in case further treatments are required with applicable discounts of up to 20 per cent at NIMS Medicity, Neyyattinkara.A public awareness session on liver and intestine diseases will also be held during the camp.For free registration, contact 94472 47772/93494 94922 during office hours.